Package ohos.app

Class GeneralReceiver

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.app.GeneralReceiver
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Sequenceable

    public class GeneralReceiver
extends Object
implements Sequenceable
    Provides generic callback methods for receiving results from other processes during inter-process communication (IPC).

    You can create a child class instance, override the onReceive(int, ohos.utils.PacMap) method, and send the child class instance to the peer end through IPC. The peer end then uses sendResult(int, ohos.utils.PacMap) to send the result back.

    Since:
    2

        public GeneralReceiver​(EventHandler handler)

        Parameters:
        handler - Indicates the EventHandler object. If this parameter is not null, onReceive(int, ohos.utils.PacMap) will be called on the thread of the specified EventHandler. If this parameter is null, onReceive(int, ohos.utils.PacMap) can be called on any thread.
